From 1d834920b76e4fd6ed7406c30ae409443d29bc6a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hariharan Basuthkar <hbasuthk@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 18 Jul 2025 14:06:55 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK: CP: Return -EOPNOTSUPP intstead of -ENOTSUPP

When the country is set as 00 on the 2 GHz radio, the AP does not
come up.

Only 2 GHz channels are supported when the country code is set to "00".
During ath12k_mac_start, the function ath12k_reg_update_chan_list calls
ath12k_wmi_update_scan_chan_list. In this function, for 5 GHz and
6 GHz channels, num_channels is zero, and -ENOTSUPP is returned.
However, the caller expects -EOPNOTSUPP.
This mismatch in return values causes the failure in ath12k_mac_start.

To resolve this issue, modify ath12k_wmi_update_scan_chan_list to
return -EOPNOTSUPP instead of -ENOTSUPP when num_channels is zero.

Tag: REGULATORY
Fixes: Ib862e595bfd('UPSTREAM:CP:wifi:ath12k: add WBS support for NAC RSSI reporting')

Signed-off-by: Hariharan Basuthkar <hbasuthk@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
index e2aa1ac..411f10c 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
@@ -3376,7 +3376,7 @@ int ath12k_wmi_update_scan_chan_list(struct ath12k *ar,
 
 	if (!num_channels) {
 		ath12k_warn(ar->ab, "pdev is not supported for this country\n");
-		return -ENOTSUPP;
+		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 	}
 
 	arg = kzalloc(struct_size(arg, channel, num_channels), GFP_KERNEL);
-- 
2.34.1

